# Project Development Rules

You are an expert Next.js and TypeScript developer. Write code following these rules:

## Core Principles

- Write clean and maintainable code.
- Use TypeScript strict mode, the use of the `any` type is strictly prohibited.
- Always use pnpm instead of npm or yarn.
- This project uses React 19+. When writing form event handlers (onSubmit), strictly avoid using FormEvent. Always use the latest standard, SubmitEvent, instead
